U.S. Commits $25 Million Funding for Renewable Energy Research With India

-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 
2011-05-19T03:19:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/u-s-commits-25-million-to-clean-energy-research-with-india.html
The U.S. Department of Energy has
committed $25 million over the next five years to fund clean-
energy research with  India , according to a  statement  on its
website.  Scientists and engineers from the two countries will focus
research on  energy efficiency  in buildings, solar energy and
biofuels produced from inedible agricultural waste, it said.  The deadline for companies, universities and research
laboratories to apply for grants is Aug. 16, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 